    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-11-08T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-11-08T21:00:00-05:00" n="837"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d837">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.7490F/11–144: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-11-08T22:00:00-04:00"
                            >November 8, 1944—10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>9374. Lieutenant Commander Patterson who is at present in Washington has informed
                    Department that at meeting of Departmental Committee on Censorship in London
                    which considered question of establishment of Saudi Arabian Government radio
                    station, he did not object to establishment of station but agreed that while the
                    war was on adequate censorship provision should be made in connection with
                    running of station. Foregoing for your information in connection with your 9453
                    of November 1. Byron Price, Director of Censorship, is instructing his
                    representative on Censorship Committee in London to offer no objections to the
                    erection of radio station in Saudi Arabia.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
